tasks.task: Analyze and Address Fruiting Issues in Fig Trees

subtasks.text: Recognize that hormone balance is critical for fruiting in fig trees.
Understand that summer pruning is necessary for fig trees, unlike other fruit trees.
Learn the proper timing for pruning fig trees (during summer for some varieties, winter for others).
Identify the difference between heading cuts and thinning cuts in pruning.
Practice thinning cuts for fig trees during the winter to maintain hormone balance for fruiting.
Consider summer pruning to encourage fruiting in some fig varieties if done properly.
Protect fig trees from winter damage to preserve hormone balance for fruiting.
Be patient with young fig trees as some varieties may take longer to fruit.
